==English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|en|pride cometh before a fall}}, {{l|en|pride goes before a fall}}, {{l|en|pride goeth before a fall}}, {{l|en|pride wenteth before a fall}}

===Etymology===
Probably from:
* '''1611,''' [[w:King James Version of the Bible|King James Version of the Bible]], [[w:Book of Proverbs|Book of Proverbs]], [[s:Bible (King James)/Proverbs#Chapter 16|16:18]],
*: Pride goeth before destruction, and an haughty spirit before a fall.
* see also, James 4:6 (KJV) But he giveth more grace. Wherefore he saith, God resisteth the proud, but giveth grace unto the humble.
* and,  1 Peter 5:5 (KJV) Likewise, ye younger, submit yourselves unto the elder. Yea, all of you be subject one to another, and be clothed with humility: for God resisteth the proud, and giveth grace to the humble.

===Proverb===
{{head|en|proverb}}

# A person who is [[proud]] will often suffer a [[setback]] or [[failure]], because of [[overconfidence]].

